
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-plugin-ubuntu` baraye nasb va modiriat plugin-haye HP dar Ubuntu estefade mishavad. In plugin-ha be shoma komak mikonand ta printer-ha va scanner-haye HP ra be rahati setup va estefade konid.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu`  --> 🚀  Rahandazi barnameye nasb be soorate graphic (GUI)
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu -i`  --> 📥  NAsb plugin az file ya URL (masalan az internet)
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu -u`  --> 📤  Hazf plugin nasb shode.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu
    
    🔹 Rahandazi barnameye nasb plugin HP.

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu -i /tmp/hplip_plugin.run
   
    🔹 Nasb plugin az file `/tmp/hplip_plugin.run`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu -i
 
    🔹 Dastoor, shoma ra be samt yek wizard hadayat mikonad ta plugin ra be rahati download va nasb konid agar hich addressi dade nashavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-plugin-ubuntu` command is used to install and manage HP plugins in Ubuntu.  These plugins help you easily set up and use HP printers and scanners.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu`  --> 🚀 Launch the plugin installation program graphically (GUI).
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu -i`  --> 📥 Install the plugin from a file or URL (e.g., from the internet).
    🔹 `hp-plugin-ubuntu -u`  --> 📤 Uninstall a plugin that has already been installed.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu
    
    🔹 Launches the HP plugin installation program.

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu -i /tmp/hplip_plugin.run
    
    🔹 Installs the plugin from the file `/tmp/hplip_plugin.run`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-plugin-ubuntu -i
    
    🔹 The command will guide you through a wizard to easily download and install the plugin if no address is specified.
